results.name: Number of not necessarily connected 3-regular simple graphs on 2n vertices with girth at least 6.
comment: The null graph on 0 vertices is vacuously 3-regular; since it is acyclic, it has infinite girth.
link: Jason Kimberley, Index of sequences counting not necessarily connected k-regular simple graphs with girth at least g
mathematica: etr[f_] := Module[{b}, b[n_] := b[n] = If[n == 0, 1, Sum[Sum[d f[d], {d, Divisors[j]}] b[n - j], {j, 1, n}]/n]; b];
xref: 3-regular simple graphs with girth at least 6: A014374 (connected), A185236 (disconnected), this sequence (not necessarily connected).
Not necessarily connected k-regular simple graphs with girth at least 6: A185326 (k=2), this sequence (k=3).
Not necessarily connected 3-regular simple graphs with girth *at least* g: A005638 (g=3), A185334 (g=4), A185335 (g=5), this sequence (g=6).
Not necessarily connected 3-regular simple graphs with girth *exactly* g: A185133 (g=3), A185134 (g=4), A185135 (g=5), A185136 (g=6).
